				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hey all,
<br />

<br />
First time posting as I have just recently began my expedition on tinkering.  Love my gnome and have always wanted to be a tinkerer.
<br />

<br />
Got a question though.  I am currently at a skill of 122 after doing glove combines and am about to start on Geerlok Brewing Devices.  I plan on farming a large quantity of porous mineral blocks in the area of roughly 500ish over the next week or so.  My question is:
<br />

<br />
With roughly 500 combines starting at a skill of 122 with a 251 int, bout how high do you think that will take me.  Am I going to be potentially looking at maxing out Geerloks? so long as I don't hit on a stretch of 100-200 combines for 1 pt?  Just kinda curious.  
<br />

<br />
I plan on doing other combines in there just so my trader can open up his market of sellable items ( ie...other geerloks, a few happy dragons, meteorlogical rockets, spyglasses, collapsables, etc etc ) but I plan on skilling up major using these Brewing Devices.  I've also got about 3-4 backpacks full of the belts of leathery fungus which I'll use after farming should I not hit that 215 number.  I've been having some good luck.  I went from 50 - 122 last night in about 2 hrs using about 1.2kpp or so.  
<br />

<br />
Great site, have been reading over it thoroughly the past few days.  Thanks!<br />_________________<br /><img src="images/smiles/bad.gif" alt="bad.gif" border="0" /> Giordiino Gnomercy <img src="images/smiles/bad.gif" alt="bad.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />
54 Enchanter on Ayonae Ro
<br />
(107) Research / <img src="images/smiles/argue.gif" alt="argue.gif" border="0" /> / (211) Tinkering</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Giordiino on Thu Feb 05, 2004 11:06 am, edited 1 time in total</span></td>
