			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can only give my personal numbers skilling up. From 135 to 215 I kept a combine log and did only the brewing geerlok. Or at least 97% of it since I'm too cheap to skill up on the others. My count was 616 combines for 80 skillups. That includes a rather dry run around 200ish skill. This was with 255 int so pretty close to yours and your estimate.
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure how much I've spent skilling up but it was a lot cheaper than I expected. I'd estimate no more than 3.5k tops from 0 to 215, and counting in the platinum looted from the netheribians (whom I never ever want to see again! EVER!) I pretty much paid for all my skilling up with two sales of corking devices. That's not counting the pre-skillup purchases I've made, that is the items I've been buying beforehand in anticipation of post 215 skilling.
<br />

<br />
If you do camp the neth bring booze. I maxed three characters on AT farming the bleedin' things and my druidess got nicknamed 'cave elf' in the process. So far I have to say tinkering takes a lot more fun farming on the whole than other tradeskills - as in more interesting places and mobs than say smithing. After the netheribians that is.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
