				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Agreed, I had the same motive with my skillup run. I have more time than platinum and have more paitence dealing with 20 green con mobs than 20 green players - so farming suits me better than raiding. <img src="images/smiles/winky.gif" alt="winky.gif" border="0" /> I did a few of the other geerloks but before I got started I wrote down cost for each geerlok and saw there was no way I'd go through first  roughly 80 skillups doing those, then the research geerlok, and then tinkering. (coiled springs aren't common or cheap enough on my server that skilling up on them is realistic for me)
<br />

<br />
Took just over two weeks, and I bought up any porous block I saw for 7pp or less. Due to the nonstacking I'd say I only managed to buy around 60 blocks or so, the rest were farmed or I traded buffs to people xping for them. I averaged around 40 blocks per day not counting the bought ones, several hours each day and I didn't kill as much as I could have since sometimes I was leaving mobs up for groups in the area. Was very streaky, some times I'd clear every single spawn and get no block, others I'd get 7 on a clearing. But by the time I trivialed them it had all evened out more or less. All in all I'm pleased I took this skillup path. May have slowed down my xping a bit but it was very cheap and I have had much worse camps.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
